Another approach to learning from limited labeled data is meta-learning. We define “meta-learning” as learning from a few demonstrations, or leveraging information from k tasks to learn task k + 1. This is opposed to meta-learning to describe outer-inner loop optimization more generally and areas of research such as Neural Architecture Search. GPT-3 [4] demonstrates an impressive few-shot learning ability where the task is demonstrated in the input context window, such as “example 1: label 1; \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
